verbose_text: In the current study, in addition to the factors such as serum albumin level, performance status and number of metastatic sites, which are in consensus with previous studies [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR], we identified two new independent prognostic factors among patients with unfavorable CUP, corrected serum calcium level (> = 10.7 mg/dl), an indicator of poor outcome, and palliative chemotherapy, an indicator of better outcome.
